text: usage: wfenable <pattern match expression for workflow names> ... This command enables one or more workflows. With this command you compare a single pattern match expression, or several, with the full workflow name, <folder>.<workflowconfigurationname>.<workflowname> , of all the workflows. The command accepts standard wild cards, such as '*' and '?'. For further information see Textual Pattern Matches . Return Codes Listed below are the different return codes for the wfenable command: Code Description 0 Will be returned if the command was successful. 1 Will be returned if the argument count is incorrect. 2 Will be returned if the user is not found or not logged in. 3 Will be returned if no matching workflow was found.
